[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/roman_keycard"]
[Student "S"]
{Your 4\D bid is a Splinter Bid, showing opening hand strength, at least 4 \Ss, and a singleton or void in \Ds. Partner bids 4NT.  

You have 2 Key-Cards, the \SK and the \CA. So do you bid 5\H?

No. You have two Key-Cards <b>AND</b> a void. So you bid 5NT. Partner bids 6\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "W"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "W:KQJ.AT76.AQJ.QJ9 32.J32.87643.843 AT8.K984.K9.KT65 97654.Q5.T52.A72"]
[Declarer "W"]
